    WHEN 494 THEN 'AI notes: Skydo''s founder Movin shared insights about their experience as an early customer of TruFides, an AI startup in the compliance and fraud detection space. This conversation provided valuable feedback about TruFides'' product, founders, and market positioning for a potential investor. Background and Relationship: - Movin knew Devang (TruFides co-founder) from PhonePe where Movin hired the first batch of APMs - Skydo became TruFides'' first non-crypto customer about a year ago - Implementation occurred approximately 4-5 months ago - Skydo pays about ₹80K (1/10th the cost of a compliance team member at ₹8L CTC) Problem and Solution: - Cross-border payments face money laundering risks requiring negative media screening - Traditional process: Compliance team manually reviews negative media articles - TruFides solution: AI reads articles and extracts key information to: - Disambiguate identities (is it the same person?) - Assess crime seriousness and transaction relevance - Reduce review time from 10 minutes to 10 seconds per case Results and Impact: - Solution "works beautifully" as Skydo''s "first AI win" - Saves approximately one full-time compliance person - Compliance head is satisfied with the implementation - Became a precedent for other AI adoption within Skydo Competitive Assessment: - TruFides vs. Fravity (Elevation Capital investment): - TruFides was immediately focused on a specific use case - Fravity was "all over the place" initially with too many use cases - Fr...'
